The discovery surface is fully discriminated:

* Each resource gets a :class:`{{ entries[0].resource_class }}`-style
  Pydantic class with a ``Literal["<slug>"]`` ``resource`` field.
* Each filter field gets its own subclass with a ``Literal["<field>"]``
  discriminator and a narrowed ``values`` descriptor.
* The top-level :data:`RegisteredResource` and per-resource filter
  unions use ``Field(discriminator=...)``, so an OpenAPI client
  reading these schemas narrows on ``resource`` / ``field`` / ``kind``
  without a runtime type check.

Generated at codegen time from each resource's filter modifier and
its ``searchable`` opt-in.  Re-run ``foundry generate`` after
adding a resource or field.
